Title: Statistical Origin of Black Hole Entropy in Matrix Theory
Authors: David A. Lowe
Comments: 9 pages, harvmac, (v2 References added, typo fixed), (v3 Some
  clarifying comments added.)
Report-no: BROWN-HET-1113
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev.Lett. 81 (1998) 256-259
\\
  The statistical entropy of black holes in M-theory is considered. Assuming
Matrix theory is the discretized light-cone quantization of a theory with
eleven-dimensional Lorentz invariance, we map the counting problem onto the
original Gibbons-Hawking calculation of the thermodynamic entropy.
